# QMD Environment Variables
# Copy to ~/.config/qmd/.env and fill in your API keys.
# Loaded automatically at startup — no need to source.

# ============================================================
# ⭐ RECOMMENDED: local embed with the night-winning tuning
# ============================================================
#
# This config beats MemPalace's published 96.6% LongMemEval _s n=500
# headline by 1.8pp (our sr5 = 98.4% overall, 100% multi-session).
# See docs/ROADMAP.md "Night 2026-04-13 → 2026-04-14" metric audit.
#
# Copy-paste these 4 lines to ~/.config/qmd/.env and you're done:
#
# QMD_EMBED_BACKEND=transformers
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_MODEL=mixedbread-ai/mxbai-embed-xsmall-v1
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_DTYPE=q8
# QMD_VEC_MIN_SIM=0.1
#
# Why each one:
# - transformers backend → local ONNX via @huggingface/transformers
#   (no cmake, no GPU required, ~50MB model download on first use)
# - mxbai-xs q8 → 384-dim quantized encoder, ~2.9s per query on CPU,
#   tested 98.2-98.4% sr5 on LongMemEval _s n=500
# - QMD_VEC_MIN_SIM=0.1 → overrides the adaptive cosine floor with
#   a fixed lower bound. The adaptive `max(0.05, top1 × 0.5)` rejects
#   too aggressively on q8 models because their cosine distribution
#   is tight (top1 ≈ 0.8 → floor 0.4 → pool = ~10 memories). Fixed
#   0.1 keeps the pool at ~40-50 memories and adds +0.2pp sr5 on
#   top of the already-beat-MemPalace baseline.

# ============================================================
# Local embed backend
# ============================================================
#
# QMD_EMBED_BACKEND=transformers   Enable local ONNX embed via
#                                  @huggingface/transformers. Off by default.
#                                  When unset, embed goes through the remote
#                                  provider configured below.
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_MODEL=...       HF repo id, e.g.
#                                  mixedbread-ai/mxbai-embed-xsmall-v1
#                                  (default; other shortlisted models in
#                                  docs/ROADMAP.md / docs/EVAL.md).
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_DTYPE=q8        q8 | fp16 | fp32 | q4 | int8 | uint8.
#                                  q8 is the sweet spot: fastest + highest
#                                  sr5 in our 2026-04-14 sweep.
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_FILE=           Override ONNX file name (omit .onnx) —
#                                  e.g. model_quint8_avx2 for the MiniLM-L6
#                                  uint8 ceiling-fallback variant.
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_QUIET=on        Suppress HF download progress bars.
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_CACHE_DIR=      Model cache location. Defaults to
#                                  ~/.cache/qmd/transformers.
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_DEVICE=         cpu | webgpu | dml | gpu | auto (default
#                                  unset = CPU). `gpu` aliases webgpu. `auto`
#                                  probes the GPU + driver + NPU and picks
#                                  device + microbatch + workers automatically
#                                  (see src/llm/gpu-probe.ts, embed-sizer.ts).
#                                  On small models (<200 MB) CPU q8 is fastest;
#                                  WebGPU only wins when the model overruns the
#                                  CPU int8 path (embgemma-300m etc.).
# QMD_TRANSFORMERS_AUTO_PREFER=cpu Force CPU even when `auto` would pick GPU.
# QMD_EMBED_QUERY_PREFIX=          Override auto-detected query prefix
# QMD_EMBED_PASSAGE_PREFIX=        Override auto-detected passage prefix.
#                                  E5 / Nomic / BGE-instruct / Jina families
#                                  are auto-detected by model id and their
#                                  standard prefixes ("query: ", "passage: ",
#                                  "search_query: ", etc.) applied at embed time.

# ============================================================
# Provider modes
# ============================================================
#
# Each operation (embed, rerank, query expansion) is configured independently
# with 4 env vars:
#
#   QMD_{OP}_PROVIDER=   api | url | gemini  (or shorthand alias)
#   QMD_{OP}_API_KEY=    Bearer token
#   QMD_{OP}_URL=        see below
#   QMD_{OP}_MODEL=      model name
#
# Provider types:
#   api     — OpenAI-compatible base URL. Paths auto-appended:
#             URL + /embeddings, URL + /rerank, URL + /chat/completions
#   url     — direct endpoint URL, used as-is (nothing appended)
#   gemini  — Google Gemini (x-goog-api-key auth, different format)
#
# Shorthand aliases (set provider + default URL automatically):
#   siliconflow → api + https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1
#   openai      → api + https://api.openai.com/v1
#   zeroentropy → url + per-operation ZeroEntropy endpoints
#   dashscope   → url + https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-api/v1/reranks

# ============================================================
# Example A: ZeroEntropy embed + rerank (one API key)
# ============================================================
#
# QMD_EMBED_PROVIDER=zeroentropy
# QMD_EMBED_API_KEY=ze-your-key
# QMD_EMBED_MODEL=zembed-1
# QMD_RERANK_PROVIDER=zeroentropy
# QMD_RERANK_API_KEY=ze-your-key
# QMD_RERANK_MODEL=zerank-2

# ============================================================
# Example B: Nebius embed + query expansion, ZeroEntropy rerank
# ============================================================
#
# QMD_EMBED_PROVIDER=api
# QMD_EMBED_API_KEY=nebius-key
# QMD_EMBED_URL=https://api.studio.nebius.ai/v1
# QMD_EMBED_MODEL=Qwen3-Embedding-8B
# QMD_RERANK_PROVIDER=zeroentropy
# QMD_RERANK_API_KEY=ze-key
# QMD_RERANK_MODEL=zerank-2
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_PROVIDER=api
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_API_KEY=nebius-key
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_URL=https://api.studio.nebius.ai/v1
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_MODEL=meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct

# ============================================================
# Example C: SiliconFlow all three operations
# ============================================================
#
# QMD_EMBED_PROVIDER=siliconflow
# QMD_EMBED_API_KEY=sk-your-key
# QMD_EMBED_MODEL=Qwen/Qwen3-Embedding-8B
# QMD_RERANK_PROVIDER=siliconflow
# QMD_RERANK_API_KEY=sk-your-key
# QMD_RERANK_MODEL=BAAI/bge-reranker-v2-m3
# QMD_RERANK_MODE=rerank
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_PROVIDER=siliconflow
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_API_KEY=sk-your-key
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_MODEL=zai-org/GLM-4.5-Air

# ============================================================
# Embedding
# ============================================================

# QMD_EMBED_PROVIDER=              # api | url | siliconflow | openai | zeroentropy
# QMD_EMBED_API_KEY=your-key
# QMD_EMBED_URL=                   # api: base URL (e.g. https://api.studio.nebius.ai/v1)
#                                  # url: full endpoint (e.g. https://api.zeroentropy.dev/v1/models/embed)
# QMD_EMBED_MODEL=                 # e.g. Qwen3-Embedding-8B, zembed-1
# QMD_EMBED_DIMENSIONS=            # Any positive integer (e.g. 2560, 4096, 1536)

# ============================================================
# Reranking
# ============================================================

# QMD_RERANK_PROVIDER=             # api | url | siliconflow | openai | zeroentropy | dashscope | gemini
# QMD_RERANK_API_KEY=your-key
# QMD_RERANK_URL=                  # api: base URL → appends /rerank  |  url: full endpoint used as-is
# QMD_RERANK_MODEL=                # e.g. BAAI/bge-reranker-v2-m3, zerank-2
# QMD_RERANK_MODE=rerank           # rerank = dedicated rerank API (default for url provider)
#                                  # llm    = chat model reranking (default for api/gemini)

# ============================================================
# Query expansion
# ============================================================

# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_PROVIDER=        # api | url | siliconflow | openai | gemini
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_API_KEY=your-key
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_URL=             # api: base URL → appends /chat/completions  |  url: full endpoint
# QMD_QUERY_EXPANSION_MODEL=           # e.g. zai-org/GLM-4.5-Air, meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct

# ============================================================
# Provider reference
# ============================================================
#
# ZeroEntropy  (https://zeroentropy.dev)
#   Embed:   https://api.zeroentropy.dev/v1/models/embed   (or eu-api.zeroentropy.dev)
#   Rerank:  https://api.zeroentropy.dev/v1/models/rerank
#   Models:  zembed-1 (embed), zerank-2 (rerank)
#
# SiliconFlow  (https://cloud.siliconflow.cn — free tier)
#   Base URL: https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1  (or https://api.siliconflow.com/v1 outside China)
#
# Nebius  (https://studio.nebius.ai)
#   Base URL: https://api.studio.nebius.ai/v1
#   Recommended embed model: Qwen3-Embedding-8B
#
# Gemini  (https://ai.google.dev — free tier: 15 RPM / 1M tokens/day)
#   Base URL: https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com
#   Model: gemini-2.5-flash
#
# OpenAI / any OpenAI-compatible endpoint
#   Base URL: https://api.openai.com/v1

# ============================================================
# Chunking  (sensible defaults)
# ============================================================

# QMD_CHUNK_SIZE_TOKENS=900        # tokens per chunk (default 900)
# QMD_CHUNK_WINDOW_TOKENS=200      # search window for break points (default 200)

# ============================================================
# Retrieval tuning — vector gate + levers
# ============================================================
#
# QMD_VEC_MIN_SIM=0.1              # ⭐ RECOMMENDED with q8 embed models.
#                                  # Override the adaptive cosine floor with
#                                  # a fixed value. Unset → adaptive
#                                  # max(0.05, top1 × 0.5), which rejects
#                                  # too aggressively on tight-cluster q8
#                                  # encoders. Fixed 0.1 keeps the candidate
#                                  # pool at ~40-50 memories (vs ~10) and
#                                  # +0.2pp sr5 on the LongMemEval _s n=500
#                                  # night sweep.
# QMD_VEC_K_MULTIPLIER=3           # k = max(limit, limit*N) for vec KNN.
#                                  # 3 is the default; bump to 20+ only if
#                                  # partition key isn't available.
# QMD_RECALL_RAW=on                # Skip all post-RRF boosts (keyword /
#                                  # quoted phrase / temporal / dialog
#                                  # diversity / query expansion / LLM
#                                  # rerank). Eval-mode flag — use for
#                                  # baseline comparisons.
#
# --- Multi-session levers (all off by default, workload-specific) ---
#
# QMD_MEMORY_EXPAND=entities       # Zero-LLM sub-query fan-out on proper
#                                  # nouns in the question. +1pp r5 on
#                                  # mxbai-xs, null on arctic-s.
# QMD_MEMORY_EXPAND=keywords       # Same fan-out but on top-N extracted
#                                  # keyword clusters (no proper-noun
#                                  # dependency — better on LongMemEval).
# QMD_MEMORY_MMR=session           # Session-diversity MMR via
#                                  # applyDialogDiversity. Null signal on
#                                  # LongMemEval because session-granular
#                                  # ingest already gives diverse top-5.
# QMD_MEMORY_SCOPE_NORM=rank       # Per-scope rank-based score
#                                  # normalization. Noop on single-scope
#                                  # queries like LongMemEval; valuable for
#                                  # multi-project qmd deployments.
# QMD_RECALL_KG_RAW=on             # RAW-compat gate for KG-in-recall.
#                                  # Only fires when query has entities and
#                                  # top-1 score < 0.3. Rare on q8 models
#                                  # where cosines cluster around 0.7+.

# ============================================================
# Scoring tunables  (advanced — defaults work well)
# ============================================================
#
# QMD_RERANK_CANDIDATE_LIMIT=40    # max docs sent to reranker
# QMD_RRF_K=60                     # RRF smoothing constant (higher = flatter ranking)
# QMD_WEIGHT_FTS=2.0               # BM25 list weight in RRF fusion
# QMD_WEIGHT_VEC=1.0               # vector list weight in RRF fusion
# QMD_BLEND_RRF_TOP3=0.75          # RRF/rerank blend for rank 1-3 (higher = trust RRF more)
# QMD_BLEND_RRF_TOP10=0.60         # blend for rank 4-10
# QMD_BLEND_RRF_REST=0.40          # blend for rank 11+
# QMD_STRONG_SIGNAL_MIN_SCORE=0.85 # BM25 score to skip expansion
# QMD_STRONG_SIGNAL_MIN_GAP=0.15   # gap between top-1 and top-2 to skip expansion

# ============================================================
# Paths  (auto-detected, override if needed)
# ============================================================

# QMD_CONFIG_DIR=~/.config/qmd    # config directory (index.yml location)
# XDG_CACHE_HOME=~/.cache         # cache dir (db at $XDG_CACHE_HOME/qmd/index.sqlite)

# ============================================================
# Eval-time knobs (only consumed by evaluate/longmemeval/eval.mts)
# ============================================================
#
# Answer-prompt shape:
# QMD_PROMPT_RULES=v11             # v10 minimal · v11 full (default) · v11.1 + ORDERING/DURATION/COUNTING · v12 CoT + Cited · v13 minimal paper-aligned (recommended for LLM-judge runs)
# QMD_ANSWER_TOP_K=5               # Top-K memories fed into answer prompt (retrieval still returns 50 for metric computation)
# QMD_ANSWER_MAX_CHARS=6000        # Per-memory char cap for the answer prompt. LongMemEval sessions average 8,283 chars — the 2026-04-17 bump from 800→6000 was required to stop the LLM from answering "no information" when the right session was retrieved but truncated.
#
# Reflection pre-pass (opt-in, +1 LLM call/question):
# QMD_RECALL_REFLECT=on            # Or use `--reflect` CLI flag.
# QMD_REFLECT_TOP_K=10             # Memories fed to reflection
# QMD_REFLECT_MAX_CHARS=800        # Per-memory char cap in reflect prompt
#
# LLM-judge (runs after every prediction when --judge is set):
# POE_API_KEY=sk-poe-...           # Required when --llm poe or --judge poe. Needs active Poe subscription.
# QMD_POE_MODEL=gpt-4o             # Generator model on Poe (override per run)
# QMD_SKIP_PREFLIGHT=on            # Skip the 16-token pre-flight quota probe (not recommended)
